# little-internet — give this Pi a unique hostname
#
# Every card flashed from the same image defaults to the hostname "pi-node", so
# multiple nodes collide on pi-node.local and mDNS renames them unpredictably
# (pi-node-2.local, …). Set a unique name here and this card comes up as
# <name>.local on first boot — headless, before mDNS advertises.
#
#   1. Copy this file to "little-internet-hostname.txt" in this same folder
#      (just drop the .example from the name).
#   2. Replace the placeholder below with this node's name. Use a short DNS
#      label: letters, digits, and hyphens only; no spaces, dots, or
#      underscores; must start and end with a letter or digit; 63 chars max.
#      Good: pi-a, pi-b, node-01, gw1.  Bad: pi_a, "pi a", -pi, pi-.
#   3. Eject the card and boot the Pi; reach it at <name>.local
#      (e.g. ssh pi@pi-a.local).
#
# Unlike the Wi-Fi file, this one is NOT deleted on first boot: a hostname isn't
# secret, it's read every boot so it stays authoritative, and the file doubles
# as a physical label for the card. To rename later, edit this file and reboot.

pi-CHANGEME
